Note:
COBOL Emitter - Buffered output for COBOL code generation

All buffer management, character/string emission, and indentation logic
is delegated to the shared byte-buffer foundation in emitter_common.runa.
COBOL-specific helpers (division/section/paragraph headers, period,
comma) are retained and built on top of the shared primitives.

Conventions:
- 4-space indentation for free-format COBOL
- Null-terminated output strings
:End Note

Import "../emitter_common.runa" as EmitterCommon

@Reasoning:
Typed view of the shared 24-byte raw header for COBOL-specific code
sites. Storage is managed by emitter_common.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Three Integer fields (buffer/capacity/length) at offsets 0/8/16 matching
the raw header layout.
@End Implementation

Type called "CobolEmitter":
    buffer as Integer
    capacity as Integer
    length as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Named constructor preserving the COBOL-specific spelling. Single hook for
future divergence (e.g. fixed-format columns 1-72 layout).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_create.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_cobol_emitter" returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_create from EmitterCommon
End Process

@Reasoning:
Paired destructor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_destroy.
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope:
Caller must drop the emitter pointer after this call.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "destroy_cobol_emitter" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_destroy from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Reserve capacity for a known-large block of output to avoid intermediate
growth events.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_ensure_capacity.
@End Implementation

Process called "ensure_capacity" takes emitter as Integer, needed as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_ensure_capacity from EmitterCommon with emitter, needed
End Process

@Reasoning:
Append a single byte. Hot helper for COBOL punctuation (period, comma).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_emit_byte.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_char" takes emitter as Integer, char as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, char
End Process

@Reasoning:
Append a null-terminated string. Used for COBOL keywords and verbs.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_emit_string.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_string" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit text followed by a newline. COBOL is line-oriented so this is a
common pattern at end-of-statement.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the string then a LF byte (10).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_line" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Named newline emitter.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits a single LF (byte 10).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_newline" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single-space helper for token separation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits a single SP (byte 32).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_space" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
End Process

@Reasoning:
Free-format COBOL allows arbitrary leading whitespace; we standardise on
4 spaces per nesting level for readability.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Loops level * 4 times emitting a space byte.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_indent" takes emitter as Integer, level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: 4-space indentation for free-format COBOL.
    Let total_spaces be level multiplied by 4
    Let count be 0
    While count is less than total_spaces:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
        Set count to count plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: COBOL-specific Helpers
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Emit '.' - COBOL's statement terminator. Centralised so the byte can
be changed if a different dialect requires it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits byte 46.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_period" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit period (.) - statement terminator in COBOL.
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 46
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit ',' - item separator in COBOL clause lists.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits byte 44.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_comma" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit comma (,) - item separator.
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 44
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit a COBOL division header line "NAME DIVISION." followed by LF.
Divisions partition the COBOL source (IDENTIFICATION / ENVIRONMENT /
DATA / PROCEDURE).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the division name, then " DIVISION", then '.' (46), then LF (10).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_division_header" takes emitter as Integer, division_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit COBOL division header: "NAME DIVISION." + newline.
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, division_name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, " DIVISION"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 46
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit a COBOL section header "NAME SECTION." + LF. Sections subdivide
divisions.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the section name, then " SECTION", then '.' (46), then LF (10).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_section_header" takes emitter as Integer, section_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit COBOL section header: "NAME SECTION." + newline.
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, section_name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, " SECTION"
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 46
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emit a COBOL paragraph header "NAME." + LF. Paragraphs are the
innermost named code units inside sections (called by PERFORM).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the paragraph name, then '.' (46), then LF (10).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_paragraph_header" takes emitter as Integer, para_name as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit COBOL paragraph header: "NAME." + newline.
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, para_name
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 46
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Snapshot the buffer into a heap-allocated null-terminated copy.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_get_output. Caller owns the returned allocation.
@End Implementation

Process called "get_output" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Expose current write position.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_length.
@End Implementation

Process called "get_length" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_length from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Reuse the buffer for a fresh translation.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_reset.
@End Implementation

Process called "reset" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_reset from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process
